		"name": "üìö Bookstore API ‚Äì Postman Collection",
		"description": "This collection demonstrates a **Spring Boot Bookstore application** that integrates **Spring Security, REST, and GraphQL**.\n\nIt is designed to showcase **authentication, authorization, and book management workflows.**\n\n---\n\n### üîë Features\n\n1. **Authentication & Registration (REST Endpoints)**\n    \n    - Users can **register** and **log in**.\n        \n    - Authentication is required before accessing protected GraphQL features.\n        \n2. **GraphQL Endpoints (Protected)**\n    \n    Accessible only after login with a valid JWT token:\n    \n    - **Book Management**\n        \n        - Add a new book (requires `STAFF` role).\n            \n        - Add book copies (requires `STAFF` role).\n            \n    - **Borrow & Return**\n        \n        - Borrow a book copy (requires `STAFF` role).\n            \n        - Return a borrowed copy (requires `STAFF` role).\n            \n    - **Filtering & Queries**\n        \n        - Filter books by user.\n            \n        - Filter books by author.\n            \n        - Filter available book copies.\n            \n        - Both `STAFF` and `MEMBER` users can query/filter.\n            \n\n---\n\n### üõ†Ô∏è Collection Structure\n\n- **REST ‚Üí Authentication**\n    \n    - `POST /register` ‚Üí Register a new user.\n        \n    - `POST /login` ‚Üí Obtain authentication token.\n        \n- **GraphQL ‚Üí Bookstore Features**\n    \n    Each major feature (e.g., add book, borrow, return, filters) is provided as a **separate GraphQL**",
